These spinach and cheese polenta muffins make an excellent addition to
anyone's lunchbox and making them is a great activity for you and the kids.
Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Email Print
1 roasted red capsicum, skin and membrane removed, sliced
1. Whisk together the milk, oil, egg and chives.
2. Place remaining ingredients into a large bowl, mixing until well combined.
3. Pour in milk mixture and stir until just combined.
4. Spoon between 12 x 1/2 cup capacity lightly oiled muffin pans and bake at 200°C for 15 minutes or until golden.
Muffins are a great way to boost our vegetable intake. Experiment by adding
grated carrot or zucchini, capsicum or baby spinach. Make a batch of mini
muffins on the weekend and freeze for your lunchbox throughout the week.
